mething to do, something to love, and something to hope for.\n\n- George Washington Burnap, The Sphere and Duties of Woman: A Course of Lectures\n|\nIf you can be aware that you have a living body, and notice when there's tension in your body, that's already an important insight.\n\n- Thich Nhat Hanh, No Mud, No Lotus: The Art of Transforming Suffering\n|\nFreedom. He offered it like someone who didn't know what it meant, someone who had never had it taken away.'pg 185\n\n- Veronica Roth, Carve the Mark\n|\nThe truth is as truth shall be,We come with our own destiny.\n\n- Mira Midha, Feelings… It's Not in What They Say but What They Hide\n|\nTo become a better you, keep asking curious questions about yourself. If you lose, ask “why?”; if you win, ask “why not?\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Become a Better You\n|\nDon't just Hurry, don't just Haste. Don't just Worry, don't just Waste. Life is a Treasure, Enjoy the Pleasure.- RVM\n\n- RVM\n|\nToday, I am doing well in every aspect of my life. But, this is only because I've realized that I can do it.\n\n- Mohith\n|\n[Happiness] comes when we choose to be who we are, to be ourselves, at this present moment in our lives.\n\n- Jean Vanier, Finding Peace\n|\nWithout the support from religion--remember, we talked about it--no father, using only his own resources, would be able to bring up a child.\n\n- Leo Tolstoy, Anna Karenina\n|\nI believe that this war, upon which I entered as a war of defense and liberation, has now become a war of aggression and conquest.\n\n- Siegfried\n|\nThinking there is something better out there in the world, something worth more than you already have- of all my mistakes,that was my biggest.\n\n- Louise Candlish, Before We Say Goodbye\n|\nYou are the Truth from foot to brow. Now, what else would you like to know?\n\n- Jalaluddin\n|\nEverybody possesses knowledge and experience that is considered to be unique to them alone; therefore, everyone has something to learn from everyone else.\n\n- C W Newman,